T1  - Common risk factors in the returns on stocks and bonds
AU  - Fama, Eugene F.
AU  - French, Kenneth R.
JO  - Journal of Financial Economics
VL  - 33
IS  - 1
SP  - 3
EP  - 56
PY  - 1993
DA  - 1993/02/01/
SN  - 0304-405X
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-405X(93)90023-5
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304405X93900235
AB  - This paper identifies five common risk factors in the returns on stocks and bonds. There are three stock-market factors: an overall market factor and factors related to firm size and book-to-market equity. There are two bond-market factors, related to maturity and default risks. Stock returns have shared variation due to the stock-market factors, and they are linked to bond returns through shared variation in the bond-market factors. Except for low-grade corporates, the bond-market factors capture the common variation in bond returns. Most important, the five factors seem to explain average returns on stocks and bonds.
ER  - 

